he other day for 4k.  It was 11/23 I think, and had boiling blood as a proc.  For those that don't know boiling blood is a low resist necro dot that does 500hp dmg over 2 minutes.  Necro's are always complaining about how much aggro their dots get, so I'm wondering if this weapon might do a pretty good job of helping me keep aggro by constantly doing dmg every tick?<br>
<br>
Are there other weapons with dots as a proc?<br>
<br>
When you consider whether it would be worth buying this.  Keep in mind that I'm a lvl 46 warrior with mediocre equipment.  I'm wearing Enchanted dwarven plate with AC around 900 unbuffed.  My current weapons are a goranga spiked club at 12/24, no proc, and a Jade green axe, 17/34, also no proc.  4k would also bankrupt me, but I'd like to find a decent weapons that would hold aggro better than what I have now.  The most aggro for the pp, if you will. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naralli>Naralli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 11:42:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4825.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs weapon with a dot proc for aggro?</span><hr size=1> The weapon you looked at was probably the sword called Bloodfire. it is 11/24 and the proc is bloodboil which is a 540 DoT over 2 minutes.<br>
This weapon is rather average in generating agro for some reason. In my experience of comparing weapons, a Frostbringer ( 4k on my server )did better and a Black Blade of Torment ( under 800pp on my server )did better as well. The Black Blade of Torment is 9/22 and procs torment which Blinds the mobs and also does a small DoT.<br>
The Blade of the Black Dragon Eye is another sword that dots. It is 14/24 and the proc is a 200 DoT over 30 seconds. This sword is great agro generator as it procs often after level 50. The problem is it doesnt drop anymore so it is very hard to find and is expensive.<br>
Good luck in your weapon search.<br>
<br>
Naralli Ironsmith <br>
